// BE-069 ROOT FIX: The WebhookEndpoint model and the entire webhook
// infrastructure (including lib/crypto.ts) have been REMOVED. There was
// NO `/api/webhooks` route — the model was dead code. The WebhooksScreen
// UI rendered hardcoded fake webhooks. The lib/crypto.ts module (for
// AES-256-GCM encryption of webhook secrets) existed but was never called.
//
// A customer paying for "webhook notifications" (a Team plan feature)
// would get nothing — the infrastructure was non-functional.
//
// Root fix: Remove the model and the crypto module. When webhooks are
// added to the roadmap, they should be implemented as a COMPLETE feature:
//   1. CRUD /api/webhooks routes
//  2. Webhook delivery service with retry logic
//   3. UI for managing endpoints
//   4. Encrypted secret storage (lib/crypto.ts or a proper KMS)
//
// NOTE TO FUTURE DEVELOPERS: If adding webhooks, create a NEW migration
// that adds the WebhookEndpoint table back. Do NOT reuse this removed
// model without the full feature implementation.
//
// REMOVED: model WebhookEndpoint { ... }
